        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'The Board of Directors chair needs a verbal opening script for a high-pressure session covering the 38% late papers and 17 overdue resolutions. Write a 90-second opening statement that acknowledges the underperformance directly, explains why late Board papers, overdue resolutions, and a growing disclosure watchlist ahead of quarter-end matter most, and signals immediate corrective action without sounding defensive. End with 3 talking points to use if directors challenge management credibility.'},
        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Prepare a stakeholder communication map for the 38% late papers and 17 overdue resolutions and the upcoming Board of Directors. Identify the priority audiences, the message each audience needs, the timing, and the main communication risk if the message is mishandled. Present as a RAG table with Red for immediate same-day communication needs, Amber for 24-hour needs, and Green for monitor-only audiences.'}
